# Logging

## Logger

- One logger per module: **`logging.getLogger(__name__)`**, or a thin wrapper (e.g. `get_logger(__name__)`) that adds JSON formatting to **stdout** for CloudWatch/Datadog later.
- Do **not** depend on an external “common lib” logger — keep formatting in-repo (`utils/logging_config.py`).

## Context

When available, include **user id**, **request id**, and **tenant/business id** in log **extra** dicts. Setting **request id** once in middleware is enough; services can log business context.

## Where to log

1. **Router** — single INFO line per meaningful call (method, path, key ids) — avoid huge bodies.  
2. **Service** — entry + failure paths; important state changes.  
3. **DAO** — optional DEBUG/INFO for slow or critical queries; avoid logging every CRUD in hot paths.

## Levels

- DEBUG — development / verbose tracing  
- INFO — normal flow and audit-worthy events  
- WARNING — recoverable oddities  
- ERROR — failures requiring attention  

## What not to log

Passwords, refresh tokens, API keys, full payment PANs, or full third-party payloads with PII.

## What not to do

- Do not use `print()` in application code paths  
- Do not duplicate the same context on every nested call if middleware already attached request id  
